column2: Clear sky- light chop- water depth 22'.
Sunny- light chop- previous several days of rain and high wind.
Wind-15 to 20 mph- sunny- hot- pleasant day.
Sunny- light chop- heavy wind and rain previous night.
Hazy- light chop- a bit of green starting to develop in the water.
Sunny- light chop- more green (blooms) appearing in lake.
Sunny- calm- the lake is taking on a greenish color- so the weeds must be blooming.
Sunny- very hazy- light chop- 8 previous. days had wind- rain t-storms.
Sunny- light chop- water mildly green.
Sunny (hazy)- light chop- not quite as much bloom in the water.
Sunny- light chop.  Last three days high winds and white caps.
Sunny- calm.  Yesterday was very windy.
Sunny- light chop.  Day after some turbulent weather with light rain.
Partly sunny- light chop.  Rained during the night along with wind and lightning and thunder.
Sunny- choppy- water starting to turn green (slightly).
Sunny- calm- slight green but mostly blue.
Sunny- calm- water only slightly green- little boating activity.
Clear- sunny- light chop- 36 degrees. at 6: 00 a.m.
Partly sunny- light chop- preceded by heavy winds.
Partly sunny- calm- 70 degrees.- last week a lot of rain.
Sunny- light chop- no rain- 70 degrees.
Sunny- calm- 84 deg.- 3 wks since rain.
Sunny- light chop- 64 deg.- following a lot of wind.
Calm- sunny- 65 F- previous 3 days very windy - no rain.
Light chop- sunny- 65 degrees. could see eagles nesting.
Calm and cloudy- 65 degrees F.- 3" rain during previous night.
Sunny- 70 degrees F.- calm and beautiful.
Clear- calm- and there was a severe windstorm the previous night.  Could see eagles nesting.
Partly cloudy- calm- and there has not been any wind for several days.  Saw eagles feeding.
Clear- slight chop on the water- and the reading is following two days of rain and wind.
Partly cloudy- light chop on the water- and there has been nice weather all week.
Partly cloudy- still- and the lake is very green near the shore.
Clear- temperature is 60 degrees- and light breeze.
Clear- temperature is 88 degrees- light breeze- and light chop.
Partly cloudy- temperature is 85 degrees- breezy- and choppy.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
55 F- dark clouds.  15-20 mph winds NW.  Choppy water.
80 F.  Partly cloudy- 10-15 mph winds- choppy
75 F- hazy sun.  20-25 mph winds.  White caps.
thunderstorm earlier in day- hazy- little wind- 70F
partly sunny- medium to heavy chop- saw geese and chicks swimming- 2 eagles
clear and calm. Wind and rain night before reading
cloudy- light chop- saw four loons in middle of lake (adults)
Overcast with 5-10 mph winds out of the SE. Temperature about 58 degrees.
Partly cloudy- wind out of the SW at 10 mph- 55 degrees and a choppy surface.
Sunny with light south winds 5-10 mph.  75 degrees and a beautiful day.
Partly sunny- light winds out of the South- 77 degrees and a slight chop on the water.
Mostly cloudy and cool with a temperature of 68 degrees- SW wind about 10-15 mph with a slight chop on the water.  Saw 2 adult loons and one of them took off flying.
Cloudy- 75 degrees and humid with very light winds. Saw a loon surface with a pan fish in it's mouth and then 2 loon's flew overhead.
Mostly sunny with high- thin clouds. 75 degrees and calm wind.
Sunny and calm with a temperature of 60 degrees- a beautiful fall day.  I saw a large fish jump while doing the temperature readings.
Sunny with a light breeze and 50 degrees- a beautiful fall day!  Saw one of the young loons swimming close to the boat.
Sunny and 55 degrees with a very light wind.
Sunny and very light winds with a temperature of 60 degrees.  Heard loons calling.  There was popal tree fuzz on the lake.
Sunny and 64 degrees with a SW wind at 10-12 mph.  We saw a loon with a fish that he quickly swallowed and dove back under for more.
Mostly sunny and 75 degrees with a SW wind about 10mph.
Mostly sunny and 75 degrees with a light wind out of the NW.
SE wind at 5 mph.  Sunny and 82 degrees.  Algae bloom seems to be starting.  Saw a fish jump and a bald eagle flying near the north shore.
SE wind again at 5-10 mph.  Mostly sunny and 70 degrees.  Water is starting to look a little murky.
Wind out of the SE at 10 MPH.  Sunny with not a cloud in the sky and 70 degrees.
Water surface looks like pea soup near the shore.  68 degrees and sunny with light and variable winds out of the NE.
Mostly sunny with very light wind out of the SE.
Sunny and 52 degrees with a NE wind at 5 mph.

70 degrees and partly sunny with winds out of the SW at 5-10 mph.  Saw the lake's pair of loons swimming near the boat. 70 degrees and partly sunny with winds out of the SW at 5-10 mph.  Saw the lake's pair of loons swimming near the boat.
Cloudy and 72 degrees with wind out of the SE at 5-10 MPH.
Sunny and humid with a temperature of 83 degrees on it's way to a high of 97.  Hardly a cloud in the sky and the wind was calm.
Mostly sunny and 72 degrees.  Windy out of the SE at 10-15 mph.
Cloudy and 62 degrees with wind out of the West at 8-10 mph.
Sunny and 80 degrees and humid.  Winds out of the SW at 8 mph.
Sunny skies and 70 degrees.  Calm winds and a smooth lake.  Saw and adult loon with one young loon.
Mostly sunny and 70 degrees with a very light wind.  Saw an eagle dive out of a pine tree and take a fish.
Sunny and 70 degrees.  Winds very light.  Saw a loon dive near the deep hole.
Not a cloud  in the sky and 75 degrees.  Very light wind from the West.  There was popal fuzz on the surface.  We saw a loon close to the boat on the ride in.
Cloudy and 59 degrees with a very light NW wind.  Saw a loon flying and heard fish jumping.
Clear sky and 65 degrees with a very light North wind at 4-8 mph.  Saw an osprey looking for fish.
Mostly sunny and 72 degrees.  Wind NNW at 5-10 mph.
82 degrees and mostly sunny.  SE wind at 5 mph.  We saw an eagle take a fish from the lake.
64 degrees and sunny with a NE wind @ 5 mph.  Beautiful day!
60 degrees and not a cloud in the sky.  Near calm conditions and saw a loon right next to the boat.
10 mph wind out of the South.  Saw an eagle fly right over the boat as Don was picking me up.  Partly cloudy.
Mostly sunny and 67 degrees.  Wind from the East at 5-10 mph.  Saw a loon surface in our boat wake.
Mostly cloudy and 53 degrees.  NEwind at 10 mph that increased to 15-20 mph while we were out there.
Partly cloudy and 70 degrees with a strong SE wind at 10 mph +.  We saw a group of 3 bald eagles fly over.  Lyle Holm was a guest.
Partly cloudy and 64 degrees with an Easterly wind at 5-10 mph.  We saw the adult loons and one baby chick.  Also saw a bald eagle perched high in the pine on the north shore.
78 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind was out of the west at 5 mph.
72 degrees and sunny.  Wind was light to 5 mph out of the West.  Saw the 2 adult loons and their baby.
Mostly cloudy and 72 degrees with very light and variable wind.  Lake was calm.
Mostly sunny and 62 degrees with a light and variable wind.  Just an absolutely beautiful fall day!
Mostly cloudy and 58 degrees with a NW wind at 3-5 mph.  We saw 2 loons.  Very nice day.
Cloudy and a cool 53 degrees with a SE wind at 5 mph.
Mostly sunny and a cool 62 degrees with a SW wind 5-10 mph.  I heard a loon call.
Sunny and not a cloud in the sky.  70 degress with winds light and variable.  We saw an eagle fly overhead.
79 degrees and partly cloudy.  NE wind at 5 mph- just a beautiful day.  We saw 3 adult loons in the water and one fly overhead.
75 degrees and mostly sunny.  NE wind at 5 mph.  Saw 2 adult loons.  It was just a beautiful day again!
Just a perfect day!  70 degress with hardly a breeze.  The water was like a mirror.
Sunny and 72 degrees- another beautiful day!  Wind was west at 5 mph.
Sunny and 64 degrees.  Winds are light and variable out of the north.
Sunny and 52 degrees.  Calm and a perfect fall day!
60 degrees and mostly cloudy with very light wind from the East.  Saw a couple of loons diving for fish.
71 degrees and partly cloudy with a south wind at 5 mph.  Very nice day.
70 degrees and mostly sunny.  NNW wind @ 10 mph.  Saw eagles and loons.  Very nice day.
62 degrees and mostly sunny with no wind.  A perfect day!  We saw and heard loons.
63 degrees and not a cloud in the sky!  Another perfect day.  Saw an eagle flying and one sitting in the tall pine on the north end of the lake.
75 degrees and hazy sun with a light overcast.  SW wind 10 mph.
68 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind out of the SW at 5-10 mph.
57 degrees with a NW wind @ 8 mph.  Mostly clear.  A beautiful fall day.
Mostly sunny and 67 degrees with a light and variable wind from the SE.
Partly sunny and pleasant.  73 degrees with a south wind at 7 mph.
Partly sunny and 75 degrees.  Winds light and variable with hardly a ripple on the lake.  Beautiful day!
65 degrees and mostly sunny- a beautiful day!  Light NW wind at 5 mph.
65 degrees and overcast.  NW wind at 5 mph.  Saw the loon chick with it's parents.
73 degrees with high hazy clouds.  Light winds out of the south at 5 mph.
63 degrees and mostly sunny with fall in the air.  Wind NW 3-5 mph.  We saw a loon and heard them calling.

75 degrees and sunny with a light and variable wind.  Juvenile loon was hanging close to the boat and diving and surfacing- also looked like it expected us to feed it.  Bob Baker came along today to learn what we do.
Mostly sunny and just a beautiful day.  Light winds out of the east.  We saw a large group of ducks.
66 degrees with sunny and clear skies.  Light and variable wind from the NE.  We saw a loon diving.
64 degrees and partly cloudy and clearing from the east.  East wind 10 mph gusting to 17 mph at the start- but it calmed down to about 5-10 mph out of the east.
69 degrees and mostly cloudy.  Light SE wind at 5 mph.
77 degrees and mostly sunny.  WNW winds at 5-10 mph and calmed to 5 mph before we were done.  Beautiful day.
69 degrees and mostly cloudy.  E wind at 10 mph.
73 degrees and mostly sunny.  WNW wind @ mph.
76 degrees and cloudy.  Wind was light and variable.
66 degrees and a high hazy cloud layer.  Winds SSW @ 5 mph.  Saw 2 new born eagles flying and playing in the air with an adult eagle.
55 degrees- cloudy and gray.  A fall like day.  Wind NNW @ 6 mph.
70 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind SS# @ 5 mph.  Just a beautiful day!
54 degrees and mostly cloudy with a high thin layer of clouds.  Wind SSE @ 4 mph.  We had some boat issues today.
Mostly sunny with high thin clouds.  64 degrees and SSE wind @ 5 mph.  Frank and Mary Hull helped me today.
61 degrees and barely a cloud in the sky- just a beautiful day!  NW wind @ 2 mph.  Bright blue sky above.
54 degrees and partly sunny but clouds look to be moving in.   Wind NE @ 7 mph.
81 degrees and partly sunny.  WSW wind @ 7 mph.
63 degrees and low- dark clouds.  NNW wind @ 5-10 mph.  More like a fall day today.
88 degrees and mostly sunny.  SSE wind @ 7 mph.  Heard loons calling and saw 3 eagles soaring above the north shore.
76 degrees and sunny.  Wind WNW @ 5-7 mph.  Very nice day.
81 degrees and partly cloudy.  South wind @ 11 mph.
63 degrees and hardly a cloud in the sky- just a beautiful day!  Near calm wind.
64 degrees and mostly cloudy with no wind.  The lake was like a mirror.  Saw an eagle take a fish from the water on the north shore.
72 degrees and not a cloud in the sky.  SSE wind @ 10 mph.  Beautiful day!
Partly sunny and 50 degrees.  ENE wind at 5 mph.
64 degrees and mostly cloudy.  Wind ENE at 5-10mph.  Saw an eagle sitting in the large white pine on the north end of the lake.
Bob Baker also collected data today but that was not an option for some reason above.  71 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind ENE @ 7 mph.  Very nice day!
Please add Bob Baker as a data collector.  I cannot chose both of us like I have in the past.  80 degrees and mostly sunny. South wind at 8 mph.  The lake was busy due to the Holiday.
80 degrees and mostly sunny.  ESE wind at 5-7 mph.
Bob Baker assisted.  Mostly sunny and 73 degrees.  Wind NE @ 7-9 mph.  Saw an
Mostly sunny and 67 degrees.  Wind ENE @ 7 mph.
Partly sunny and a cool 59 degrees.  Fall is in the air.  Wind NNE @ 7 mph.
71 degrees and sunny.  A beautiful day!
69 degrees and sunny with a mild NE wind @ 3 mph.  Beautiful day! Saw a pair of loons.
69 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind out of the WSW @ 7 mph.  Saw a couple of eagles soaring.
79 degrees and mostly sunny with high thin clouds.  Wind ESE @ 8 mph.
86 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind SE at 3-5 mph.  Saw 2 loons but no baby chicks.
78 degrees and mostly sunny- nice day.  Wind WNW @ 8 mph.  Saw eagles soaring in the wind.
77 degrees and wind SW @ 2 mph.  Mostly cloudy.  A very nice day.
64 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind ESE @ 5 mph
Mostly sunny and a nice day.  57 degrees and wind out of the NW @ 7 mph.  Saw a few ducks on the lake.
Sunny with hardly a cloud in the sky.  Wind N @ 4 mph.  Just a beautiful day.  Several boats enjoying the lake- both fishing and recreation.
Sunny and 73 degrees- just a beautiful day!  Wind SSW @ 1 mph.  Saw an osprey fly overhead.
70 degrees and not a cloud in the sky.  Wind WSW @ 10 mph.  Saw a loon.
79 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind ESE @ 3 mph.  Very nice day.  Saw the loons with 2 babies that are getting pretty big.
67 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind N @ 8 mph.  Another beautiful day!  Saw the loon family but only 1 baby so it looks like we lost one of them.
79 degrees and mostly cloudy.  Wind ENE @ 4 mph.  Muggy day despite the clouds.
70 degrees and cloudy.  Wind SW @ 5 mph.
81 degrees and mostly sunny.  Winds south at 3 mph.  Heard several eagles and the loons.  Beautiful day!
70 degrees and partly sunny.  Wind light and variable- the lake was smooth as glass- just a beautiful day!  We saw bald eagles and heard the loons.
70 degrees and mostly sunny.  Wind WSW @ 3 mph.  Heard both the eagles and loons calling.  Very nice morning!
70 degrees and sunny.  Wind W @ 12 mph.  Water had a brown color to it today.
46 degrees with hazy sun from the wildfires out west.  Wind NE @ 3mph.
